description:
That’s a ~27,000 difference. The CDC added the total death rate, excluding pneumonia and flu deaths. It’s a significant difference. Even though the total number of deaths included suspected deaths, it still looks like it’s on par with flu deaths, which account for about 80,000 deaths each year. Suspected deaths include those who tested negative but had CV symptoms like asthma, respiratory and heart issues, and those who weren’t tested. .
.
Surprisingly, this is on the CDC’s website, yet the news is still going with 64,382. .
.
On April 11, the total death rate (minus pneumonia & flu) was 11K, and the total amount (with pneumonia & flu) was 54K, which the news was reporting. .
.
Which amount do you think should be reported? .
.
.
